==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cider
<hw>Ci"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>cidre</ets>,
OF. sidre, fr. L. <ets>sicera</ets> a kind of strong drink, Gr. <?/; of
Oriental origin; cf. Heb. <ets>sh⟦amac⟧kar</ets> to be intoxicated,
<ets>sh⟦emac⟧k⟦amac⟧r</ets> strong drink.]</ety> <def>The expressed
juice of apples. It is used as a beverage, for making vinegar, and for
other purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Cider</xex> was formerly used to signify the juice
of other fruits, and other kinds of strong liquor, but was not applied
to wine.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cider brandy</b></col>, <cd>a kind of brandy distilled
from cider.</cd> -- <col><b>Cider mill</b></col>, <cd>a mill in which
cider is made.</cd> -- <col><b>Cider press</b></col>, <cd>the press of a
cider mill.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ciderist</ent>⟦br⟧
